# Assignments are Reactive ‚ö°

To update state, just assign a new value.

```javascript
let count = 0;
function increment() {
  count += 1; // Direct assignment triggers update
}
```
No `useState`, no `this.setState`, no `count.value`.

# The $: Syntax üí≤

To make a variable *depend* on another (like `computed` in Vue):

```javascript
let count = 0;
$: doubled = count * 2;
$: console.log(count);
```
Whenever `count` changes, `doubled` re-calculates automatically.

# If / Else üîÄ

Logic lives in the HTML, wrapped in curly braces.

```html
{#if user.loggedIn}
  <button on:click={logout}>Log out</button>
{:else}
  <button on:click={login}>Log in</button>
{/if}
```

